# Env files. Per Lovable docs (https://docs.lovable.dev/integrations/cloud),
# the frontend build reads VITE_* vars from a COMMITTED .env — NOT from Secrets —
# so .env must NOT be gitignored in this project. .env holds ONLY public /
# publishable VITE_* values (never secret keys). The .local / .production
# variants stay ignored for genuine local-only secrets and overrides.
.env.local
.env.production
.env.*.local

